00:00:00.256 --> 00:00:03.320
<b>In Safety In Motion there are three leverage zones.</b>

00:00:03.321 --> 00:00:03.868
<b>green,</b>

00:00:03.869 --> 00:00:04.675
<b>yellow,</b>

00:00:04.688 --> 00:00:05.708
<b>and red.</b>

00:00:06.144 --> 00:00:08.292
<b>Each zone is based on your elbow position,</b>

00:00:08.293 --> 00:00:09.728
<b>not your hand position.</b>

00:00:10.496 --> 00:00:12.752
<b>As your elbow moves away from your side,</b>

00:00:12.753 --> 00:00:14.080
<b>in any direction,</b>

00:00:14.336 --> 00:00:15.872
<b>you’re working in your yellow zone.</b>

00:00:16.384 --> 00:00:19.240
<b>If your elbows moves more than six inches </b>
<b>away from your side, </b>

00:00:19.241 --> 00:00:21.152
<b>again in any direction,</b>

00:00:21.250 --> 00:00:22.785
<b>you’re operating in your red zone.</b>

00:00:23.296 --> 00:00:24.052
<b>Remember,</b>

00:00:24.066 --> 00:00:26.323
<b>most activities can be done in your red,</b>

00:00:26.324 --> 00:00:26.960
<b>yellow</b>

00:00:26.961 --> 00:00:28.161
<b>or green zone.</b>

